{"type":"message","id":"86925a7f","parentId":"45a0b366","timestamp":"2026-03-14T15:31:32.241Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The \"exec\" action is not recognized. Let me look at the available actions again: list, poll, log, write, send-keys, submit, paste, kill.\n\nMaybe I need to use a different approach. Perhaps I should try using \"write\" without a pre-existing session to see if it creates one, or maybe I need to use \"submit\" first.\n\nActually, looking at the tool description more carefully, it says \"Manage running exec sessions\". This suggests sessions need to be created externally first, perhaps through a different mechanism.\n\nLet me try a different approach - maybe I can use web_fetch to fetch news from a news website directly, or try web_search again with different parameters.\n\nActually, let me try web_search again with English query since the fetch failed before - maybe it was a network issue.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2f080ba2aa7e46cabd05a077","name":"web_search","arguments":{"count":5,"freshness":"month","query":"March 2026 latest news"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"dashscope-coding","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773502286702}}
