{"type":"message","id":"7e8fac26","parentId":"912a97f3","timestamp":"2026-03-14T15:31:53.723Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I see that both web_search attempts failed with \"fetch failed\" errors. Let me try a different approach.\n\nSince I'm having trouble with the search tools, let me check if there are any other ways to get news from March 2026. However, it's important to note that we're currently in 2024 (based on the system context), so searching for news from March 2026 would be looking for future events, which don't exist yet.\n\nThis is actually impossible - there can't be real news from March 2026 since that date hasn't occurred yet. The user is asking for news from a future date.\n\nGiven this realization, I should explain that news from March 2026 doesn't exist yet since we're still in 2024, and therefore no search tool will return actual news results for that time period.\n\nAs a subagent tasked with searching for \"2026 年 3 月最新新闻\" (latest news from March 2026), I need to report back that this search cannot yield real results because March 2026 hasn't happened yet.\n\nLet me complete my task by reporting this finding to the main agent."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"dashscope-coding","model":"qwen3-max-2026-01-23","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773502304895}}
